<Author>pgrabar
<Content>Great Location For Chase Field Games Two friends and I stayed here in late Sept. 2008, mainly to be within walking distance of Chase Field, home of the Arizona Diamondbacks. The hotel is just 3 blocks away from the ball park, an easy walk. It saves time and money not having to deal with the hassle of parking. On the way is a nice pub, the Rose and Crown, which features excellent lunches during the day, and a wide variety of drinks at night. The hotel itself, besides being in a handy location, has many things going for it. The airport shuttle was prompt, just 12 minutes to arrive. The breakfast area is large, and besides the usual cold items, also has hot waffles, eggs, and sausage. The rooms have a desk area, a sofa and chair opposite the desk area, a small wet bar, fridge, and counter, comfortable beds, a separate bathroom sink area, and a good shower, complete with a real mat. The staff were all helpful and friendly. All in all, an excellent hotel at a good rate and location. I'd certainly stay here again when in Phoenix. 
